  "title": "ISic002937. I.Sicily inscription 002937",
  "body": "<div id=\"editions\"><div class=\"attribution\">Unknown</div><div id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <a id=\"al1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-text=\"γυ\">γ̣υ̣</span>  <span data-text=\"μνασιάρχων\">[μνασιάρχων?]</span>  <br id=\"al2-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-text=\"Πίστωνοςτοῦ\">Πίστωνος[τοῦ]</span>  <span data-text=\"Πυθοδώρου\">[Π]υ̣θ̣ο̣δ[ώρου</span>  <span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>] <br id=\"al3-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span><span data-text=\"τοῦ\">τοῦ</span>  <span data-text=\"Εὔξιος,\">Εὔξιος,</span>  <span data-text=\"Ζωΐλου\">Ζωΐλου</span>  <span data-text=\"τοῦ\">το[ῦ</span>  <span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>] <br id=\"al4-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span><span data-text=\"νεανίσκοι\">νεανίσκοι</span>  <span data-text=\"λαμπαδισταὶ\">λαμπαδιστ[αὶ</span>  <span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>] </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Unknown</div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\"><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><a id=\"al1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-text=\"γυ\">..</span><span data-text=\"μνασιάρχων\">[..........]</span><br id=\"al2-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-text=\"Πίστωνοςτοῦ\">ΠΙΣΤΩΝΟΣ[...</span><span data-text=\"Πυθοδώρου\">.]...Δ[....</span><span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<br id=\"al3-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span><span data-text=\"τοῦ\">ΤΟΥ</span><span data-text=\"Εὔξιος,\">ΕΥΞΙΟΣ</span><span data-text=\"Ζωΐλου\">ΖΩΙΛΟΥ</span><span data-text=\"τοῦ\">ΤΟ[.</span><span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]<br id=\"al4-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">4</span><span data-text=\"νεανίσκοι\">ΝΕΑΝΙΣΚΟΙ</span><span data-text=\"λαμπαδισταὶ\">ΛΑΜΠΑΔΙΣΤ[..</span><span dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---</span>]</span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2><a href=\"ISic002937_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, courtesy Museo della cultura e delle Arti Figurative Bizantine e Normanne\" src=\"ISic002937_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic002937.jpg\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, courtesy Museo della cultura e delle Arti Figurative Bizantine e Normanne\" src=\"ISic002937-thumb.jpg\"></a><a href=\"ISic002937_leftthreequarter_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, courtesy Museo della cultura e delle Arti Figurative Bizantine e Normanne\" src=\"ISic002937_leftthreequarter_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic002937_leftthreequarter.jpg\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, courtesy Museo della cultura e delle Arti Figurative Bizantine e Normanne\" src=\"ISic002937_leftthreequarter-thumb.jpg\"></a><a href=\"ISic002937_rightthreequarter_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, courtesy Museo della cultura e delle Arti Figurative Bizantine e Normanne\" src=\"ISic002937_rightthreequarter_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic002937_rightthreequarter.jpg\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, courtesy Museo della cultura e delle Arti Figurative Bizantine e Normanne\" src=\"ISic002937_rightthreequarter-thumb.jpg\"></a></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span><span>Text of Manganaro 1999</span></span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2> translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\">  </p><p>  </p></div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p>One of two inscriptions on this upright stone, broken in its upper right area. The other inscription, on the front face upper left is <a href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001412\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001412</a>. Cf. IG XIV.369-71 for other evidence of gymnasion in Haluntium. The text of Manganaro is ambitious and requires revision in light of fresh autopsy</p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li> 49.1270 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796</a></li><li> 26.1060 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796</a></li><li> Manganaro 1965 202 tav.73.1-2 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001841\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001841</a></li><li> Moretti 1976 182 n.2 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001736\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001736</a></li><li> Cordiano 1997 43-45 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002064\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002064</a></li><li> Manganaro 1999 65 no.54 fig.136 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001813\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001813</a></li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"> <p>Plain letters of the middle Hellenistic period: Pi has verticals of equal length; sigma has parallel top and bottom strokes; omicron is small and mid-line; epsilon has a short middle stroke; mu has vertical first and last strokes, while the middle point only descends part way; alpha has both broken and straight bar</p> <p> Types list: <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Α-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Α type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Α-type1.3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Α type1.3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Δ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Δ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2.3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2.3.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ε-type2.3.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ε type2.3.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Κ-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Κ type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Κ-type1.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Κ type1.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Κ-type1.4.html\" target=\"_blank\">Κ type1.4</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Μ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Μ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Μ-type2.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Μ type2.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ν-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ν type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ν-type1.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ν type1.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ο-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ο type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Ο-type1.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ο type1.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Π-type1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Π type1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Π-type1.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Π type1.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Σ-tyoe3.2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Σ tyoe3.2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Σ-type3.html\" target=\"_blank\">Σ type3</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Τ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Τ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Τ-type2.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Τ type2.1</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Υ-type2.html\" target=\"_blank\">Υ type2</a> <a href=\"https://kingsdigitallab.github.io/crossreads/data/allographs/types/greek-Υ-type2.1.html\" target=\"_blank\">Υ type2.1</a> </p> Lines 1-4  9  Interlineation line 1 to 2    </div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.  </div>",
