    {
      "id": "commentary",
      "html": "<h2>commentary</h2>  <p>One of two inscriptions on this upright stone, broken in its upper right area. The other inscription, on the front face upper left is <a href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001412\" target=\"_blank\">ISic001412</a>. Cf. IG XIV.369-71 for other evidence of gymnasion in Haluntium. The text of Manganaro is ambitious and requires revision in light of fresh autopsy</p>  "
    },
    {
      "id": "bibliography",
      "html": "<h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li> 49.1270 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796</a></li><li> 26.1060 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796</a></li><li> Manganaro 1965 202 tav.73.1-2 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001841\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001841</a></li><li> Moretti 1976 182 n.2 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001736\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001736</a></li><li> Cordiano 1997 43-45 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002064\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002064</a></li><li> Manganaro 1999 65 no.54 fig.136 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001813\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001813</a></li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  "
